d 'TMPINVI': module solving Interactive Tabular Matrix Problems via Pseudoinverse Estimation (TMPinvI) program is a wrapper for the TMPinv-estimator commands tmpinv and tmpinvl2 with options extending its functionality to pre/postestimation
d
d	 This program is a wrapper for the TMPinv-estimator
d commands tmpinv and  tmpinvl2 with options extending its
d functionality to pre/postestimation. The Tabular Matrix Problems
d via Pseudoinverse Estimation (TMPinv) is a  two-stage estimation
d method that reformulates structured table-based systems - such as
d allocation problems, transaction matrices, and input–output
d tables - as structured least-squares problems. Based on the
d Convex Least Squares Programming (CLSP) framework, TMPinv solves
d systems with row and column constraints, block structure, and
d optionally reduced dimensionality by (1) constructing a canonical
d constraint form and applying a pseudoinverse-based projection,
d followed by (2) a convex-programming refinement stage to improve
d fit, coherence, and regularization (e.g., via Lasso, Ridge, or
d Elastic Net). 
d
d KW: linear programming
d KW: least squares
d KW: pseudoinverse
d KW: singular value decomposition
d
d Requires: Stata version 16, tmpinv from SSC (q.v.)
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260120
d
d Author: Ilya Bolotov, Prague University of Economics and Business
d Support: email ilya.bolotov@@vse.cz
d
f tmpinvi.ado
f tmpinvi.sthlp
